Hello, everyone, team 9059, COLTech Robotics here. We are having an issue with our radio where we can’t configure it. We’ve been able to control it via ethernet, and we were able to load firmware, but the configuration failed and threw the following error:
Configuring computer IP address
Failed to change IP Address, please check for an adapter with the address: 192.168.1.51.
We tried to ping the IP through command prompt, but we weren’t able to get anything back from it. We’ve also tried a few things through device manager and messing around with ethernet settings, but we haven’t been able to get anything to work. All advice is appreciated, and thank you for your time
